  "title": "Admin & IT Support Executive (Unipath | Programming and Coding | Office Automation) Changi",
  "description": "<p><strong>Location:</strong> Changi <br /><strong>Working Hours:</strong> 8:00 AM – 4:30 PM<br /><strong>Contract:</strong> 1-Year Contract (Renewable)<br /><strong>Salary:</strong> $30-$35 / hour </p><p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><p>We are seeking a <strong>positive, solution-oriented Admin Executive</strong> who is a strong team player to support our academic and administrative operations.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Provide administrative support to the <strong>Vice Principal’s Office, Teachers, and Tertiary-Level Courses</strong></p></li><li><p>Assist with <strong>IT setup and support</strong>, including the <strong>Computer Lab</strong></p></li><li><p>Utilize <strong>programming and coding skills</strong> to support office automation (e.g. <strong>UiPath, Microsoft Visual Studio</strong>)</p></li><li><p>Maintain <strong>student records</strong> and generate <strong>data reports</strong></p></li><li><p>Provide <strong>logistical and operational support</strong> for school events and daily operations</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><p>Positive attitude with strong problem-solving skills</p></li><li><p>Team-oriented with good communication abilities</p></li><li><p>Experience or knowledge in <strong>IT support</strong> and <strong>office automation</strong></p></li><li><p>Programming or coding skills are required</p></li><li><p>Ability to manage administrative and operational tasks efficiently<br /></p><p><br /></p><p><em><strong>“This is in partnership with the Employment and Employability Institute Pte Ltd (“e2i”).</strong></em></p><p><em>e2i is the empowering network for workers and employers seeking employment and employability solutions. e2i serves as a bridge between workers and employers, connecting with workers to offer job security through job-matching, career guidance and skills upgrading services, and partnering employers to address their manpower needs through recruitment, training, and job redesign solutions. e2i is a tripartite initiative of the National Trades Union Congress set up to support nation-wide manpower and skills upgrading initiatives. By applying for this role, you consent to RMA Groups’s PDPA and e2i’s PDPA.”</em></p></li></ul>",
